p. 49
Peter Forgasc’s exhibition at the EYE in 2013 titled ‘Looming Fire: Stories from the Dutch East Indies 1900–1940’. Forgasc appropriated home movies and other personal documents for this installation, aiming to recreate a semblance of daily life of Europeans in the Netherlands East Indies, but he admitted that he took artistic and personal licences: ‘I make compositions on the basis of the material I have found. They are personal interpretations of history, not documentaries aiming at objectivity’ (Forgasc 2013).
